news.title: Delhi: Housing society in Dwarka slapped with a Rs 2-crore water bill
news.para: “We have complained about the faulty meter to DJB’s zonal office on many occasions. We requested them to change it, but they haven’t done anything about it,” said Rajender, administrator at Kunj Vihar housing society, which does not have a residents’ association.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA may take police help to claim land for Madhuban scheme
news.para: The Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) has decided to renew its efforts to lay claim on about 700 acres for its ambitious Madhuban Bapudham housing project. The acquisition process has been hampered because of a protest by farmers from five villages about enhanced compensation.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA yet to process several land regularisation scheme applications
news.para: ​While issues like incomplete applications have been hampering the scrutiny process on the part of the VMRDA, some applicants complain of delayed processing and subsequent disposals of their applications.

news.title: Land for houses will be vetted by team of officials: Kerala minister
news.para: Replying to a submission by opposition leader VD Satheesan, who pointed out that the condition laid out in the Life Mission guidelines that the land recorded as “nilam” in revenue records cannot be purchased for Life Mission beneficiaries for house construction has caused immense difficulties, especially since land availability is very low in the state.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh to give ownership rights to urban poor in slums
news.para: ​​It said an amendment in the Himachal Pradesh Slum Dwellers (Proprietary Rights) Bill, 2022, will ensure that people occupying the government land for the last many decades are identified and given ownership rights of houses built on two biswas land.

news.title: Bengaluru: Thousands of flat owners get BBMP notice over unauthorised construction
news.para: The notice said if he failed to submit the documents by Monday evening, BBMP officials will visit his flat on Tuesday (March 15) and declare it unauthorised.

news.title: Telangana government nets Rs 179 crore on first day of land auctions
news.para: The HMDA conducted the auctions for open plots in Bahadurpally and Thorrur in HMDA limits and some plots in Narketpally in Nalgonda, Bhootpur in Mahbubnagar, Kamareddy, Gadwal in Jogulamba Gadwal district, Mavala in Adilabad and Yalal in Vikarabad district.

news.title: Housing co-operative federation moves Bombay HC against NA tax
news.para: ​All properties not coming under the “gaothan” areas as classified by the collector in accordance with the Maharashtra Land Revenue Code, 1960, would have to pay the NA tax.

news.title: Ex-RWA of Chintels Paradiso told to share complaints on construction quality
news.para: In an interaction with the probe panel formed by deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav, the residents of Tower D had pointed out that they had lodged multiple complaints with the then RWA about construction quality in their flats.

news.title: Noida: Supertech twin towers to be gone in nine seconds
news.para: Coincidentally, the nine-second demolition is nine months from the August 31, 2021 order of the Supreme Court for the two Supertech buildings – Apex and Ceyane – to be razed to the ground.

news.title: Four banks come on board to infuse funds into Amrapali housing projects
news.para: Six banks---Bank of Baroda, Punjab National Bank, Bank of India, State Bank of India, UCO Bank and Punjab & Sindh Bank--had agreed way back in November to infuse money in Amrapali’s projects but they have been dithering in taking a final decision in the last four months.

news.title: ED attached wrong properties of ex-director of Amrapali Group: Forensic auditor to SC
news.para: ​A bench of Justices UU Lalit and Bela M Trivedi was told by forensic auditor Pawan Agarwala that what ED is claiming to be the properties of Amrapali Group's former director Prem Mishra as proceeds of crime was actually the properties of Amrapali Modern Homes Pvt Ltd, which has been constructed by siphoning of home buyers money.

news.title: Sebi levies Rs 7 lakh fine on Jaypee Infratech for disclosure lapses
news.para: The company did not make disclosures with regard to series of non-convertible debt (NCD) securities issued and listed by it, as required under market norms, a Sebi order said.

news.title: Government brings clarity in policy for FDI in real estate business
news.para: According to the Press Note of the Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT) released on Monday, it is clarified that FDI is not permitted in an entity which is engaged or proposes to engage in real estate business, construction of farm houses and trading in transferable development rights.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Illegal structures double in four years in heritage zones
news.para: Between 2011 and May 2021, the core heritage zone of the AMC, which includes Khadia 1, Khadia 2, Shahibaugh, Shahpur, Jamalpur and Dariapur, saw 2,057 illegal buildings.
